Visrep had grown into a large interactive run loop with all of its real invariants trapped inside nested helpers, which made it hard to harden without either brittle terminal-puppetry tests or no tests at all. This pass pulls the stable data transforms to file scope: selection normalization, literal/pattern building, regex scanning, scope filtering, line replacement, separator selection, and selection-only replacement fallback. The interactive behavior is left in run(), but the logic now has direct seams for adjacent specs.

Coverage added in lua/scripts/visrep_spec.lua:
- marks_to_range normalizes reversed marks and computes UTF-8 exclusive ends
- build_literal_core and build_patterns encode Unicode and separate boundary vs anywhere behavior
- build_match_index scans matches against real buffer lines
- filter_by_scope covers charwise and block scope rules
- build_replaced_line / apply_replacements_by_line / replace_selected_region cover the replacement machinery
- run() integration covers default boundary mode, Tab toggle to anywhere mode, UTF-8 replacement without byte artifacts, and the multiline input path

